  "privileged_info_summary": "The autocrop task uses images sourced from Unsplash (600x400 primary, 600x338 alternative). A 50-pixel white border is added to each image using ImageMagick, resulting in 700x500 and 700x438 dimensions respectively. The task requires the agent to use GIMP's autocrop feature (accessed via Image \u2192 Autocrop Image in GIMP 2.8 or Image \u2192 Crop to Content in GIMP 2.10+) to remove these borders. The verifier expects a 5-50% area reduction, uniform border detection using standard deviation < 15, and 70% content preservation. The expected area reductions are 31.4% and 33.9% for the primary and alternative images respectively, both well within acceptable thresholds. Task has a 60-second timeout, 4 max steps, and sparse reward type.",
